LUST
    * is and intense and uncontrolled desire. Includes the uncontrolled desire for money, food, fame, or power.

GLUTTONY
    * overindulgence and overconsumption of anything to the point of waste. Excessive desire for food causes it to be witheld from the needy.

GREED
    * is an inordinate desire to acquire or possess more than one needs.
    
SLOTH
    * is sometimes defined as physical laziness, spiritual laziness. Also been defined as a failure to do things that one should do. By this definition, evil exist when good men fail to act.

WRATH
    * also known as rage, may be described as inordinate and uncontrolled feelings of hatred and anger. Wrath in it's purest form, presents with self-destructiveness, violence, and hate that may provoke feuds that can go on for centuries. May persist long after the person who did another a grievous wrong is dead. Anger can manifest in different ways, including impatience, revenge, and self-destructive behaviour, such as drug abuse or suicide.

ENVY
    * desire the entity and covet it.

PRIDE
    * considered the original and most serious of the seven deadly sins: the source of the others. It is identified as believing that one is essentially better than others, failing to acknowledge the accomplishments of others, and excessive admiration of the personal self. It also includes vainglory which is unjustified boasting.
    * pride is the deadliest of all the sins and leads directly to damnation
